File: South Africa's captain Siya Kolisi. JOHANNESBURG - Springbok captain Siya Kolisi assisted a flight attendant to explain the emergency exit procedures while on a flight to Durban. Kolisi and his team were on they to the coast as part of the next stop on the World Cup victory parade. READ: #TrophyTour2019 touches down in Durban In a video posted on social media on Thursday, Kolisi can be seen standing in the passageway pointing to all the emergency exits while giggling. The Springboks will continue on their victory parade on Friday and will be travelling through uMhlanga, Kwamashu and Durban.